Proto-Proposal : Indenture
---

Amend Rule 1714 to read :

   An Overdue Payment Order that is a number of Blots is that
   number of Overdue Blots.  A Lawless Player is a Player who has
   more than 30 Overdue Blots.

   Whenever a Player is Lawless and is eir own Executor, the Justiciar,
   or the Speaker if the Lawless Player holds the Office of Justiciar,
   shall conduct an Auction to Indenture that Player, as defined in
   other Rules. At the end of the Auction, the Herald shall vacate 
   all Blots of the Lawless Player and bill that Player for 5 
   Indulgences.

Enact a Rule, titled "Auctions", reading :

   Whenever the Rules call for an Auction to be held, the 
   Player responsible for holding the Auction shall announce that 
   fact to the Public Forum as soon as possible. For a period of one 
   Week after such an announcement is posted, all Players, 
   with the exception of any Players made ineligible by other Rules,
   may post Bids to the Public Forum.

   A Bid consists of a combination of Delayed Transfer Orders, naming 
   any number of Currencies, specifying the Bank as the destination, 
   submitted for the purpose of entering a Bid in one specific Auction,
   to be executed at end of the Auction period.

   A Bid is only valid if all amounts of Currencies named therein are 
   larger than the amounts named in all previous Bids, or if that Bid 
   names a Currency not named in any previous Bids. If one of the 
   Transfer Orders making up a Bid are cancelled, the entire Bid 
   thereby becomes invalid.

   If the Auction being held is designated by the Rules as an Open 
   Auction, only Bids sent to the Public Forum shall be valid.

   As soon as possible after the end of the Auction period, the 
   Player responsible for holding the Auction shall announce the 
   identity of the Player who posted the most recent valid Bid. That 
   Player shall be known as the Winner of the Auction, and any 
   effects of the Auction specified in the Rules shall take place at 
   the time of this announcement.

Enact a Rule, titled "Auction to Indenture", reading :

   Whenever the Rules call for an Auction to Indenture a Player, all 
   Active Players, with the exception of the Player whose Indenture 
   is being auctioned, shall be eligible.

   The Winner of the Auction shall become the Executor of the 
   Indentured Player for a period of one month.

---

[Makes Lawlessness more fun, brings back echoes of the great Zombie 
Scam, introduces Auctions - a potentially useful mechanism in and of 
themselves - what more could you possibly want... ;) ]


