Oops, forgot about that. An updated proto follows.

Proto-Proposal : Indenture, v1.1
---

Amend Rule 1714 to read :

   An Overdue Payment Order that is a number of Blots is that
   number of Overdue Blots.  A Lawless Player is a Player who has more
   than 30 Overdue Blots.

   Whenever a Player is Lawless and is eir own Executor, the Justiciar,
   or the Speaker if the Lawless Player holds the Office of Justiciar,
   shall conduct an Open Auction to Indenture that Player, as defined in
   other Rules.

   At the end of the Auction, the Herald shall vacate all Blots of the
   Lawless Player and bill that Player for 5 Indulgences.

Enact a Rule, titled "Auctions", reading :

   Whenever the Rules call for an Auction to be held, the 
   Player responsible for holding the Auction shall announce that fact
   to the Public Forum as soon as possible. For a period of one Week
   after such an announcement is posted, all Players, with the
   exception of any Players made ineligible by other Rules, may post
   Bids to the Public Forum.

   As soon as possible after the end of the Auction period, the 
   Player responsible for holding the Auction shall announce the
   identity of the Winner of the Auction, and any effects
   of the Auction specified in the Rules shall take place at the time
   of this announcement.

Enact a Rule, titled "Bidding", reading :

   A Bid consists of a combination of Delayed Transfer Orders, naming
   any number of Currencies specifically defined by the Rules,
   specifying the Bank as the destination, submitted for the purpose of
   entering a Bid in one specific Auction, to be executed at end of the
   Auction period.

   A Bid is only valid if all amounts of Currencies named therein are
   larger than the amounts named in all previous Bids, or if that Bid
   names a Currency not named in any previous Bids in addition to all
   Currencies already named.

   If one of the Transfer Orders making up a Bid are cancelled, the
   entire Bid thereby becomes invalid. Recordkeepors are not allowed 
   to reject a Transfer Order that is part of the Bid solely on the 
   grounds that it is a Delayed Transfer Order, any Rule to the 
   contrary not withstanding.

   At the end of the Auction period, the Transfer Orders making up all
   valid Bids save the most recent one are cancelled. The Player who
   made the most recent valid Bid becomes the Winner of the Auction.

   If the Auction being held is designated by the Rules as an Open
   Auction, only Bids sent to the Public Forum shall be valid.

Enact a Rule, titled "Auction to Indenture", reading :

   Whenever the Rules call for an Auction to Indenture a Player, all
   Active Players, with the exception of the Player whose Indenture is
   being auctioned, shall be eligible.

   The Winner of the Auction shall become the Executor of the 
   Indentured Player for a period of one month.

---

[Makes Lawlessness more fun, brings back echoes of the great Zombie
Scam, introduces Auctions - a potentially useful mechanism in and of
themselves - what more could you possibly want... ;) ]

[v1.1 changes - clarified rule for topping previous bids, prohibited
custom Currencies, only the Winner pays.] 


