Regarding auctions, instead of using the clunky Delayed Transfer
Orders (which, if you've read the Omnibus Reform Act of 1998, I plan
to repeal), I would suggest the following:

Bidder made bids merely by communicating them to the auctioneer.  At
the end of the auction, the bids are ranked, and the highest bidder is
entitled to acquire the property by transferring the bidded amount to
the seller.  If e fails to do so within seven days, or before that
time withdraws eir interest, the next highest bidder is entitled to do
so, and so on.  If all bidders fail to pay or withdraw, the property
remains in the possession of the seller.  Title vests upon payment,
not upon completion of the auction.

This, I think, is a more reasonable approach.

