Well, repealing R833 is certainly something we could do, but there'd
be a temptation to replace it with something similar, since the
concept of rewarding Players for making Proposals that succeed (and
perhaps penalizing them for making Proposals that fail) is basically
a good one. The real problems with R833 are firstly that it gives its
rewards in P-Notes, and is in fact virtually the sole source of
P-Notes in the economy, resulting in a circular situation in which
one spends P-Notes only to get P-Notes back again, and secondly that
the amount of the award, F-A, is absurdly profligate.  

So what I would suggest is an amendment, which I'll write up later
today, awarding Players 2 VTs for each week in which they get a
Proposal passed.

