Klaus Herrmanns NB6_25(3751) wrote:
>
>Of course, abolishing disinterested proposals instead of P-notes might
>be a way to make P-notes functional again. While I would prefer the
>simplification of abolishing P-notes altogether, the abolition of
>disinterested proposals might be enough. 

It's a move I favor, because it follows the same line of reasoning
that led us to get rid of free voting. Voting and making Proposals
are the two key activities in pretty much any game of Nomic, and it
makes sense to me that we are moving toward a situation in which
each of these activities will have with a concretized Currency to
represent it, and neither of the activities are free.

