>R1504, requiring the CotC to issue a PO for one Indulgence from Morendil to the
>Bank.
>
>I'm not sure what effect this can have.  Although the appeal itself is well
>defined, the ability to initiate this kind of appeal is not.  R1564 covers the
>appeal of an existing Injunction, but not the appeal of a missing one.

Wasn't there a CFJ recently which dealt with these matters? Can anyone
dig it up?

At any rate, matters are (yet) more complicated than Crito has noticed.
R1435 states that:

      When a Rule states that a Player is to gain some number of
      Blots, a Payment Order shall be executed with that Player as
      the payor, the Bank as the payee, and for a number of
      Indulgences equal to the number of Blots that Player is to
      receive.  This order is to be executed by whomever is required
      to report the change in Blots.

Which, in this case, would be me, not the Clerk. In any case, I note that
R1504 applies to Crimes and Infractions, whereas Morendil has committed
neither a Crime nor an Infraction, but rather has been convicted of violating
a Rule (which conviction is now the subject of an Appeal). So I don't think
R1504 applies.

Since the Judgement has been appealed, I'll hold off on making the PO
for Indulgences until the Appeal is settled, unless the timing rules
require me to act sooner. Do they?


